\description{
The \pkg{dataforge} package provides tools for simulating structured data,
with a focus on factorial and mixed experimental designs commonly used in
social science and psychology research.

\strong{Core capabilities:}

\itemize{
\item \strong{Factorial design simulation}:
\code{forge_design()} generates data for within- and between-subject designs.

\item \strong{Correlated variables}:
\code{rnorm_forge()} simulates multivariate normal variables with a specified correlation structure.

\item \strong{Simulation from existing data}:
\code{forge_df()} resamples data while preserving distributional structure.

\item \strong{Mixed-effects design builders}:
\code{add_random()}, \code{add_between()}, \code{add_within()}, \code{add_ranef()}.

\item \strong{NORTA distribution simulation}:
\code{rmulti()} and \code{norm2x()} generate beta, binomial, gamma, Likert, Poisson, etc.

\item \strong{Likert scale tools}:
\code{rlikert()}, \code{dlikert()}, \code{plikert()}, \code{qlikert()}.

\item \strong{Data reshaping}:
\code{long2wide()} and \code{wide2long()}.

\item \strong{Missing data simulation}:
\code{messy()} introduces controlled missingness.

\item \strong{Visualisation}:
\code{plot_design()} creates ggplot2-based plots.

\item \strong{Codebook generation}:
\code{forge_codebook()} summarises variable metadata.
}
